### Medium-Severity Findings

#### 5. Eager Test _(Smell #5)_

**Method:** `OrderProcessor_FullWorkflow_Succeeds` (line 52)  
**Evidence:** 7 distinct production methods called — `ValidateOrder`, `CalculateTotal`, `ApplyDiscount`, `ReserveInventory`, `ProcessPayment`, `SendConfirmation`, `UpdateOrderHistory`.

```csharp
// ❌ Smelly — when this fails, which of the 7 steps broke?
processor.ValidateOrder(order);
processor.CalculateTotal(order);
processor.ApplyDiscount(order, "SAVE10");
processor.ReserveInventory(order);
processor.ProcessPayment(order, new CreditCard("4111111111111111"));
processor.SendConfirmation(order);
processor.UpdateOrderHistory(order);
Assert.AreEqual("Completed", order.Status);
```

**Fix:** Test each behavior in isolation; keep one high-level integration test if desired but test individual steps separately.

**Risk if unfixed:** Failure diagnosis requires stepping through all 7 methods.

